data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home dcor at your Albuquerque, NM Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
Worst experience ever! My fiance and I took our time shopping for the right sectional. We finally narrowed it down to Ashley Furniture. We paid in full cash for a 5k couch. This is where it goes wrong. We get our couch and it turns out one of the ends of the sectional was ripped at the bottom, ripped at seams to where the inner cotton was poking out, a huge stain on the seating cushion and didnt come with the feet. So within an hour of us receiving the item we immediately called. The store told us we had to file a claim online. Which we immediately did and that process was so unnecessarily over complicated! A week passes by and we dont hear a thing. We call the main store and told me we filed a claim online and we havent heard back. They said wait a few more days. A week 1/2 passes and still nothing. We reach out to our salesmen and he was no help. Finally my husband decided to go to the store and talked to a manager and explained his disappointment and they could care less. So we told them we wanted to return it. They told us they dont accept returns. My husband said that maybe they shouldve made us aware that this couch isnt returnable before we purchased it. Manager said its not their fault we didnt read our contract properly! So we waited longer to hear from the claims team online. Still NOTHING! At this point we decided to wrap it up and take it down to the warehouse where we picked it up from. This is where we finally got some professionalism finally! We spoke to a guy named Jonah and he kindly looked up our claim. We explained our situation and in the system it showed our claim but it was updated as deleted! So someone went into the system and specifically deleted our claim intentionally!! Jonah was so kind and helpful he helped us navigate through this and got us a new end to our sectional. Jonah was the only light to this whole situation!! Isnt that a damn shame??? You think if you spend a significant amount of money you would think a company especially as big as Ashley furniture would have some care and professionalism to their customers but they didnt! My family will never do business with them again!

I ordered a recliner and it was to be delivered on Saturday after waiting two weeks . I made arrangements for the delivery. I was called on Friday morning at 7:00 am on my day off to tell me it wasnt coming the next day instead I have to wait another 4 days and make arrangements during the week . I then called the store to speak to a supervisor because the girl that called couldnt answer any of my questions , NO ONE CALLED me back! So I called the store and spoke to ANTHONY. I was told that NO manager could talk to me cause they were ALL busy with customers that were in the store. I think ANTHONY needs to go back to training and learn that In Store or On line WE ARE ALL CUSTOMERS!!!!!!! I then had to call the 1800 number for a one man show Omar that I had him cancel my order but my refund would take 10 days. I asked again to speak to a manager or supervisor but there was no one else to talk to he was by himself. This is unacceptable. I will be calling the BBB. Just a warning if you buy something and want to cancel from ASHLEY FURNITURE because of scheduling or horrible customer service you wont get your money back for 10-12 days. This is NOT customer service . And it seems that these companies dont care if your unhappy . This is the world were living in. Unacceptable!!!!!i will NOT shop here again.

Let me start by asking you something. What is the worst guest at a house party? Is it the person that didn't read the invite correctly and arrives way too early? You bet! That is a mother-in-law move or a work-friend-with-borderline-Aspergers-you-felt-obligated-to-invite-but-hoped-woundn't-come move. You see, I scheduled my couch's arrival more than a month in advance. I took time off work to not interfere with people that "hypothetically" depend on me. I had an easy DMV appointment 10-minutes away from my house scheduled one hour prior to the EARLIEST possible delivery window provided by Ashley as I took the whole AM off. When did the delivery people first call indicating they were 10 minutes away? 1 hour and 20 minutes before the EARLIEST possible delivery time. To their credit, they weren't lying and they arrived a full one hour before the EARLIEST time they were supposed to arrive and I missed my DMV appointment...but I did get a couch that 1) I paid for the delivery which was delivered whenever they wanted not when I needed it and 2) only "wanted" in these least emphatic way...it was more of a necessity as I had no place to sit. Missing that DMV appointment required me to take more time off work and drive 1 hour and 30 minutes round-trip to the neatest DMV that had an appointment still available that day. Thanks, Ashley! Let's say, "hypotheticallly" speaking I'm a healthcare provider that has a schedule with appointments of people that depend on me being, "on time." What happens if I get ahead of schedule? Nothing! The next patients probably can't come in early because they have agency and free-will and probably also took time off of work to come and see me..."hypothetically" still, of course. In sum, there is zero credit for being early in this world (unless you are Amazon, which doesn't require you to be home) it is actually detrimental to everyone whether at a party or for an appointment. Zero Stars. Yes, the couch is fine. Yes, the delivery was fine but still, zero stars. I'd up it to one star if Ashley would refund my delivery fee and go to the DMV for me and deal with that whole non-sense. Do you know what the best part of this review is? As a GenX-er, I'm not special and it doesn't matter what I think which negates this whole review. That is juxtaposed to the generation of delivery drivers that showed-up from a certain, younger, more inwardly-looking generation that, by their own admission, are very special as the world obviously revolves around them. I hope they ended their day early to make "content" after making my day much longer.

Although I recommend Ashley overall, I do not recommend the store in Albuquerque. Last year, we ordered a lot of furniture and some was very delayed in coming in. Despite this, I tried them again because I needed to purchase a loveseat. Although it was on display/not marked as such, the model we selected was discontinued. I requested to buy the display model, and the salesperson said noone was there to make that decision (it was a Sunday) and he would call me the next day. When he didn't call me the next day, I sent him a text to which he never replied. I tried calling the store the following day, and the store didn't pick up their phone so it went to an out of country customer service line. The costomer service told me I had to call the store, they cannot help me. Of course, given the store didn't answer, my only option would be to go back to the store in person. I opted to go to a different store rather than work with the staff at the store. I have always had a good experience with Ashley in other states that I have lived, but unfortunately this one (Albuquerque) appears to have poor management and staff. Adding this on 3 August 2023 - the below response from "owner" is a canned response (as you can tell from them asking for an order number and store location) - when I texted them, I received canned responses and an update on an old order - nothing in regard to my review above. Clearly this company/store is in need of better customer service.

I am not one to leave one-star reviews and vent, but these guys are the epitome of horrendous customer service and just downright not caring about their customers once they have their money. I paid for "premium delivery" $160 to have my bed delivered and assembled. The pictures show what they left me. Since I was working, I asked my 77 year old mother to be at the house while the bed was delivered and assembled. They left me a bed with two missing slats and a missing support leg on the middle slat, rendering the bed useless since it won't support a box spring and mattress (Pics attached). The delivery guys obviously knew this but played dumb and took advantage of my elderly mother's lack of awareness. I spent two hrs on the phone the following day to demand they either complete setup or refund the $160 given they did not give me what i had paid for. Most of the two hours was spent on hold being bounced around to different people. I had to insist multiple times to speak to a supervisor. After the poor customer service kid caved and put me through, the supervisor offered me a discount on the bed that was half the amount of the supposed premium service. On principle, i said no thanks, I'm asking for a refund on something i was promised but not given. He said it was not possible and i would have to go to the location where i got the bed. The supervisor informed me that the missing parts were not available in store but would be sent in 7-10 days and upon arrival I'd get a call. We are talking about two slats and a support leg that are pretty universal and most likely on a gazillion different display models they could've borrowed from. I then drove to the Ashley location and spoke to Mara, their customer ops specialist. She logged my complaint and said i should receive the refund within 48 hrs and that she'd call me. Apparently this was just to get me out of the store. After five days or so, i called the store directly and spoke to Mara. she said that i should see a refund and to wait maybe anothwr day or so. Two days later and nothing. I called again and was placed on hold for about 10 minutes before getting sent to voicemail. This happened twice. The next day I went back to the store and spoke to Mara in person. She showed me the comms with wherever this stuff gets elevated to on the screen. There was nothing in there that showed i would get a refund, not even a response. She sent another message and said she would call me. That was last week. No call, no resolution whatsoever, no parts and we have been sleeping on a mattress on our floor dancing through an incomplete bed frame to get around our room for the past couple of weeks now. I have been stonewalled, lied to, cheated out of $160 having paid for a complete setup i didn't get, and left to have to navigate a bedroom with unnecessary space taken up by an incomplete bedframe with a mattress on the floor next to it for two weeks now. Shame on you Ashley, you are a disgrace to customer service principles, I genuinely despise you for your just not caring, complete disregard, and apparent policy of training employees to do everything possible to brush of justifiably unsatisfied customers once you have their money. I hope that this review serves as a buyer beware to others and that they take their business elsewhere as you deserve nobody's business.

NOTE: The STANDARD RESPONSE from Ashley (Owner) is useless! I have followed those general instructions since the beginning and even received a "Case Number," but it did not help. I'm still waiting for some type of resolution. I purchased a 12" hybrid mattress (firm) and boxspring from Ashley and was willing to wait a few weeks for shipment. I was sorely disappointed in the delivery AND the mattress! The delivery driver mistakenly delivered the boxspring to another customer and gave me a mattress that was warped (i.e., lumpy!) I believe he also delivered the mattress that I paid for to that same customer, but because both mattresses were queen size he didn't say anything. This is obviously not the mattress I chose in the store. This all happened YESTERDAY (1/10/23). I called customer service twice, and both calls were conveniently disconnected. However, the third time is a charm I guess. But that's not all.... The driver went back to the other customer's home and got the boxspring, but when he removed it from his truck it ripped in two places! Thinking I wouldn't notice it, he said he was going to have their tech return and staple it! What in the....! I did NOT accept the boxspring and he placed it back on his truck. Now I'm left with having to deal with customer service to pick up/replace this lumpy mattress (See photo) and deliver the new boxspring. This is absolutely unacceptable and unprofessional. Never let them deliver a mattress and boxspring unwrapped or unboxed because you never know what or whose order you are receiving! Fortunately my salesperson has been very responsive throughout this nightmare and was shocked when I sent her the picture of the mattress I received. She promised to sort this out for me today. Let's see... As I will surely update my rating if they make this right and are very responsive. I'll keep you posted! UPDATE 1-20-23 (Raised to 2 stars): Bad News: No response relating to the lumpy mattress. Waiting to hear from their "technician" to "schedule a visit." Good News: I received credit into my account on the boxspring return and the 200.00 charge that appeared on my credit card a few days ago was explained as I had forgotten that I used a separate card for furniture protection plan. By the way, the furniture (Sofa and Loveseat) that I ordered from Ashley's prior to the mattress fiasco looks absolutely amazing in my living room! And... the delivery was great! (4 Stars) But I'm still skeptical about using them again. Let's see how this mattress issue gets resolved. UPDATE 2-3-2023: As I was entering into the store to find out the status of the issue with the mattress, I saw my original sales person, Elana, practically run away, and it was obvious that she wanted to avoid me. And her colleagues were laughing at the whole situation. I informed the manager on duty of this. Meanwhile, I'm still requesting a status on the mattress issue. The Manager on Duty, E. Lovato, was very concerned and apologized for this taking so long. She said if I don't hear back from thenresolution specialist by Monday (2-6-22) she will follow through and make sure this case is resolved. Let's see! UPDATE 2-17-2023: Ashley Furniture has redeemed themselves! They delivered a replacement mattress on 2-16-2023, and the delivery was flawless. The delivery drivers were very professional, friendly, and removed the packaging material in front of me, from inside my home! They handled the mattress with extreme care and even shared information with me about inflatatable mattresses that I wasn't aware of. I am happy amd will be changing my review from 1 star to 3. It took over a month to resolve, but I'm happy that it was finally resolved. Thank you Ashley Customer Service and Management team (especially E. Lovato) for making things right.

Apparently, it is perfectly acceptable for the staff at this location to treat customers horribly. There is a lady that works here (Ashley) and she feels as if she doesn't need to give her name when asked. She will flat out tell you she doesn't have to give her name. She will also hang up the phone on her customers when she no longer wants to talk to them. The only reason I know her name is because I went to the store after she repeatedly keep hanging up on me so i went to the store across town to ask if I could talk to a manager and She told me that they are to busy to talk with customers. I asked again to speak with a manager as I was a upset customer. She did finally get me a manager. He was annoyed and was unable to help me. I did prior have a credit which we had gotten in farmington nm. There service was amazing. But as we moved to albuquerque nm. I thought they would be wonderful too. NO!!!! I was going to purchase bed room furniture for our house and use the credit with it. There failure to get my address changed in the 2 months my furniture was ordered was a huge problem. That was discovered when I got a conformation for farmington. This is why I started calling to get this fixed as I had already talked with them numerous times I had assumed it was already fixed and done. Again NO!! I was very excited to have our furniture delivered on the day that was stated. For our new home which In itself was a huge ordeal. So at this point I was told I may not have my credit for a diffrent purchase (one that i could take out of the store myself) as they can not manage to get my address correct so it is forfeited. I will never have anything to do with this corporation again. They do not value customers and allow their staff to treat customers any way.

Worst experience will not be returning back. First off when we got our furniture delivered we were missing a tall dresser to find out that they did not add it to the order I reached out to my sales agent and he stated they messed up took it off the order when I let him know I wanted a full bed set with everything it was very important that I had all the drawers the chest dresser night Stans and side night stand for each side of the bed. He said ok well come in and Ill give you a discount its going to be 874.99 for the 5 drawers chest I go in the following day and we get everything together for payment and he tells me oh I have the wrong chest in your cart its going to be 1,000.00 also it will be another delivery fee on top of that. So I was not happy that he did not disclose this in our conversation before. Then I tell him Ill just pick it up from warehouse instead. He proceeds with that he is sorry only certain qualify I guess orders qualify for white glove delivery and I asked why my order that was delivered wasnt free for white glove delivery our purchase totaled to 7k he said he wasnt sure I had pulled up the Ashley furniture website and saw that the price was less than he was telling me he was unwilling to help me with the now 2 errors they made so I left store will be looking into returning all the furniture I bought and take my business elsewhere.

UPDATE: Their response below is a joke. I did what the person said, emailed my info and issue and they NEVER responded. They don't care. Their response is just for show... If I could give NO stars I would. Horrible. I ordered 5 items from this store last year October 2021. Was told 8 - 12 weeks. By March 2022 only one item came in - a dresser. Went to the warehouse to pick it up and asked if I could see it and was told I had to sign off first. I sign, and go to the bay for loading. I ask the guy loading if he can open the box so I can see it and he said no but if there's an issue tell us within 3 days and it'll get taken care of. So take it home and unbox it to find a DESTROYED dresser. Immediately call customer service which isn't even local and get a case number. Nothing happens. Weeks go by no remedy. Finally go to the store to complain and I am offered a replacement. Told it'll be 72 hours. Nothing happens. Weeks go by again and I go back to the store. First off the girl behind the counter clearly doesn't want to help and treats me like a I am interrupting her day. I'm told they have a replacement at the warehouse but just had not contacted me yet, and by the way, they can't guarantee delivery dates for anything else I ordered. By this time I am so upset by the whole situation that I don't want any of it anymore and I tell the her to cancel everything. Says she can't cancel the dresser because I signed off on it and they will not accept return of the broken dresser there. I can schedule the replacement and that's all I can do. I ask for a manager and I'm told the manager can't help - only the people behind the service counter have the ability to do anything. So I leave the broken dresser anyway and try to remedy with the credit card co. By this time I have already gotten my first bill for the dresser. The credit card company sides with Ashley because I "signed off on it". So now I pay monthly for a $1000 dresser that I DO NOT HAVE and do not want. I either pay the monthly charge or hurt my credit. No one will help you here. You're stuck. No one will do right by the customer if you've "signed off on it". Never again will I set foot in an Ashely Home Store. Run.

I'll start by saying that the salesperson was excellent. The furniture I selected was very nice. However, when I purchased the furniture, I specifically asked if there will be a problem with delivering to the military base. They assured me there wouldn't be a problem. I expect that if they deliver to the base, they should know the rules and requirements. The first thing they did was scheduled the delivery a whole month after I purchased it. I wasn't happy about that but I said fine. On the day they were supposed to deliver, they were not allowed to enter the base because they arrived too late to register for entry. That was Saturday. They called me right away to tell me they couldn't enter for delivery and said someone would contact me to reschedule. So they call me Monday afternoon to reschedule and they wanted to schedule delivery 10 days after the original date. I told them that was unacceptable and that I shouldn't be made to wait because of their mistake. I told them that if they do not have the furniture delivered by Wednesday, they can cancel the order. They said that they won't be delivering in my area until the day they mentioned. I told them that is not my problem, that's theirs and I shouldn't be punished for their ineptitude. They said that a manager may call to discuss. The manager never called, and the order was cancelled. BUT!!! there is a charge on the account that should not be there and it's been an ordeal to get that rectified as well! It's unfortunate because I had a lot more furniture to purchase and I was going to purchase it from them. I'll never go back to Ashley Furniture again. Not even when I move to another part of the country. I promise that!

Well, I didn't think I'd be writing another bad review again for Ashley, yet, here we are. This will be one of two reviews unfortunately. We purchased a bedroom set from Ashley in May or June. The person who helped us was AlanaRae and she was AWESOME. This was her second time being our salesperson and she is always a pleasure. Some of our set arrived quickly which was great. The delivery men scratched our wood floors with the chest of drawers, but we just decided to overlook it. The second delivery was July 13th for the rest of the furniture. As you can see by the photos, the delivery men damaged our floors. This was an incident that we could not just overlook. Per usual, Ashley calls you after delivery to ensure you are pleased, and I informed the caller, Lori Augustain of the damage. She asked me to send photos of the damage which I did immediately. She said she submitted a claim and the distribution center would be in touch. After a few back and forth emails with Janelle Clark from July 14th through July 28th, they offered a payment for the damages. We accepted, and now they have gone radio silent. I mean literally ignoring us. LITERALLY. I have emailed many times, and every time CCing other people at Ashley only to continuously be ignored. I have also called many times only to have no resolution. This is VERY disheartening that their delivery men can damage your home, yet, the make no effort to compensate us and completely ignore us when we reach out. I have purchased from Ashley since 2007 because I love their furniture selections, but have never had the type of issues I have been having since purchasing from Ashley over the past year. Just... Disheartening and extremely unfortunate..

UPDATE: See the comment Ashley left below, with an offer to help and a phone number to call. Guess what, I called, there is no one who will help you - its a call center and they dont help. They will TEXT with you NOT TALK ON the phone. Said theyd have the manager of the Albuquerque store call me back, and submitted a rush ticket. No manager ever called. Do not shop at Ashley!! Customer service is HORRIBLE - youll be stuck with damaged furniture. NO STARS! Please read before you spend money at Ashley. BEWARE of Ashley Furniture. We waited for two months for a couch that was in stock - that was a bait a switch tactic. Once we got the couch, it was damaged. I witnessed the delivery driver drop the couch. Waited another 4 weeks for a replacement AND BEFORE WE LET THEM BRING INTO THE HOUSE - WE INSPECTED it in the driveway. The second couch was torn so we refused delivery. We spent hours on the phone trying to get a refund, and its impossible to get any customer service. They offered to send another couch - another four weeks. We said no because they sell defective cheaply made furniture. This is the absolute worst company. Save yourself a headache and buy a couch somewhere else. We spent two entire days waiting for delivery, spent at least 6 hours trying to get customer service - and we are still without a couch or a refund. Next stop - dispute with credit card. After this review you will see Ashley post a so sorry, please call us at this number and well help you - dont believe it - they will not help you. Its a auto reply - Ashley doesnt care about this review, but you might.

Massive headache. First issue, I was sold the coverage without my consent ~$350. Picked up the couch and when we got at home and unwrapped found out it had a significant cell defect. We have been told at the distribution center where we picked it up, that if there was anything wrong with it we could bring it back within three days and it would be replaced. I called customer service, they said I could wait a few weeks for a technician to fix the issue. I mentioned what the person at the distribution center said, and asked if I could just take it back and exchange it instead of waiting a long time for a technician. They said that that was an option as well. After moving the couch back out to the trailer, driving all the way down to the distribution center. I was informed that they do no such thing, and told to take the couch home. Ive been calling the store all day without a single response. Looking at the other reviews on here, I am very discouraged, and honestly do not expect to be able to contact the store or receive any help whatsoever. I really regret my decision, to spend so much money on what was supposed to be a very nice piece of furniture and a respectable establishment. I sincerely hope that this can be resolved, and would love to update this review if my experience with Ashley improves. Edit: I was contacted and they reversed the charge for the coverage which I really appreciated. Ive amended my rating to show this. 2nd Edit: Back to 1 star, wish it could be zero. After 3 weeks they still have not reversed the charge. Empty promises, buyer beware please take your money elsewhere!

Long review, bear with me. I have bought full living rooms full of furniture from Ashley in the past, and service was outstanding. However - in December I bought a large sectional, 8 pieces, and when it was delivered we had problems with the ottomans (top sewn in a full 2 inches off center) and bunching fabric on areas of the sectional. I called within 72 hours and started a service ticket. This was in February. Since then I have had FOUR appointments for a service tech to come look at it and had FOUR no call, no show. I have gone into the store 3 times to speak to customer service. The customer service agents have no idea why I am not getting scheduled and keep promising me that I will get a call and a visit. This has never happened. Last time I was in the store a member from a store in Santa Fe was able to get me a little further, but still no call and no service. This sure sounds like a breach of trust and on some level the contract. I have no recourse. The sales arm of Ashley is not the Service arm and can do nothing about it. I can't get any recourse and basically they are telling me there's nothing I can do about it. If it were less expensive furniture I could probably get over it, but $4500 couches should be impeccable. If they aren't they should be fixed. This is the worst service experience I've ever had. Still no resolution. If I didn't pay my bill they'd be quick to respond, but basically once you sign for that furniture, understand that you have no recourse and you are at their mercy. Horrible business model separating service from sales in this way. I should have already had this fixed, discounted or been allowed to return it and walk away. Forget about speaking to "management" because they can do nothing for you. Unbelievable.

If you want honest service go anywhere else. My wife and I went in to purchase a bed on 4/10. We picked one we liked and told the manager that we did not want to fill out the financing paperwork unless we knew it was in stock and available. Supply chain is tough for everyone right now and we didn't want to risk waiting months for a new bed when our mattress was arriving on 4/17. The manager sat down with us and looked up inventory, informing us that there were 3 sets of side rails and 3 footboards available, but the headboard we preferred was on order for June. He informed us that our second choice of headboard was available, however, so we changed to that one. Our sales associate asked when we would like it delivered (for $260!?) and we asked if 4/15 would work. We were assured it would be no problem and we would get a call by 4/13 from the team that schedules deliveries. By 4/14 we had not received a call, so I called the store. The automated system said I could schedule my delivery in 5-7 weeks. We knew the nightstands we wanted were on order and didn't mind waiting for those, so we assumed it was a mistake and I tried to speak to a person. After waiting on hold for a half hour, I gave up and drove to the store. At the store, I spoke to the manager again, who informed me that the bed would not be in stock until May 18th. This is the same manager that sat across the table from me and told me they had 3 available and in stock. He then tried to tell me they may have sold out while the paperwork was being printed. I pointedly asked if he was implying they sold 3 of the exact bed we chose in the 10 minutes it took us to sign paperwork. He backpedaled and informed me that the sales associate told him we were ok with waiting for the bed. When I asked him how we fix this he said there was nothing he could do, but I could cancel my order if I wanted. It's bad enough to directly lie to a customer to secure a sale, but to then throw your employee under the bus behind his back is terrible. I would suggest going to any other furniture store.

Long story short, we felt like the store gave us the run around. If you absolutely love something and want to order from Ashley's, we highly recommend ordering from the Santa Fe branch. We are highly disappointed with this store. If you want to hear the long story, here it is: We typically order items from Ashley's in Santa Fe, but were in Albuquerque one day and decided to order some new couches. We ordered mid August 2021, and much to our suprise, recieved a text in September with a delivery date. We expected 6-9 months due to the shortage in workers, furniture, etc. Nonetheless, we got our home ready, waited, and the delivery never came. We called Ashley's and they informed us our furniture had been discontinued but they had one couch and were just waiting on another. In February, they called to let us know our furniture was arriving. Again, we prepared, and the truck was unable to deliver. During all our phone conversations, we were transferred numerous times and were given different updates from those transfers. We drove to Albuquerque to speak with someone in person, and they could not offer any information. We were promised a phone call, and that call never came. We rescheduled for two weeks after the truck was unable to deliver. We prepared for the third time, and a day before delivery, we received a call that we needed to financially pre-qualify again because our promotional period ended; they would not be delivering. We were always willing to wait the 6-9 months of delivery, but at this point we were tired of the failed promises, lack of communication, lack of professionalism, and lack of organization. We decided to cancel our order. We are sad, but relieved to no longer be in the middle of the store's mess.

We ordered a new sectional, ottoman, and nightstands on 4/4/21 and was told it would be 12 - 14 weeks for delivery due to the pandemic, the big freeze in Texas and the ship stuck in canal in Panama. No problem because I realize things are moving at a very slow pace. Beginning of July we call to check in the status and was told it would be around 8/17/21 for delivery. As we came close to that date we call to check status and was told it would be another month. Call again in October and told that the ottoman would be delivered 11/7/21 and the sectional would be in January but the nightstands wouldnt come in until March. That day comes and goes with no update from Ashley. I believe it was 1/26/22 my husband gets a message saying that the complete order was in and would be delivered on 2/4/22. On 2/2/22 he confirmed delivery through text messages and automated phone calls for delivery on 2/4/22 between 1015 and 115. A couple of hours after the last confirmation he gets a call saying that the delivery is canceled due to weather. As far as we can see it is going to be sunny and a high in the upper 30s or low 40s for the delivery day. Who knew that furniture was undeliverable in that kind of weather. At this point in time we are completely frustrated and decide we will drive the 2 hours to Albuquerque and get our furniture ourselves. My husband then spent several hours making phone calls to try and arrange this but could not get it done because the lady he talked to at the store did not call him back and of course nobody will answer a phone there. I think it is safe to say that we are done dealing with Ashley Furniture and will not shop with them again which is a shame because we have shopped with them a few times over the past 8 years and have had a great experience.

If you want to save yourself heartache, headache, and high blood pressure spikes, do NOT shop here. The sales reps are great, but furniture is on backorder for AT LEAST 12-16 weeks, may be even longer. I purchased a living room set, complete bedroom set, and new mattress. The sales rep understood this wasn't replacement furniture as I had just moved, so I was currently without. The mattress was in-stock, so as a courtesy given the delivery delay, the store provided a bed frame and box springs (the bought bedroom furniture didn't require box springs) so I could have something to sleep on. Paid $89.99 for "white glove delivery" and scheduled delivery within 3 1/2 weeks. The delivery crew dropped the stuff in the bedroom and left. No set-up, no unpacking, no removal of debris. When I went to set-up the bed frame, the box was torn, and upon taking the parts out, was missing the extension bars for a king bed. Called customer service and filed a service ticket. If the delivery crew had done what they were paid for and assembled the frame, they would have known immediately parts were missing. Customer service stated someone would call me back. A week later, still no call back, so I called customer service again. An hour plus on the phone, being put on hold and speaking with the rep, they can't just provide extension bars (they're not in stock) so they have to deliver another bed frame. Of course the earliest delivery is a week later. I shared this experience with several friends and one told me he wished I had told him I was shopping at Ashley because he had a similar bad experience with availability and delivery and would have advised to go somewhere else. Talked with my landlord and they too had a bad experience with Ashley furniture delivery. So disappointing given the reputation of Ashley furniture, but their contracted delivery service is terrible, and when you contact the store for assistance, they state they're showroom only and warehouse and delivery are separate entities and they can't help you. The lack of customer service and aide to make things right is dismal. Customer service doesn't follow through on call backs, so you'll be making repeated attempts for resolution. Save yourself the trouble and shop anywhere else.

If I could rate lower, I would. Sales people explained to my wife that she could purchase the protection plan for the furniture. It would cover anything, we as the buyers, accidentally did to the furniture and it would be covered. Well to our surprise it was not covered. I suggest not getting the protection plan if you don't read the fine print and don't listen to the sales people when they say you are covered for anything that happens to your furniture because that is not true. We paid $789.00 and we are not covered on our current damages. Only silver lining is that if I don't use the warranty in 2 years I can get $500 in store credit because the protection plan didn't pay on any claims. I won't buy anything at Ashley's again and will definitely use that store credit if there isn't any fine print stating that I can't. Based on the negative reviews I see those customers were treated the same. I believe the response from the manager or owner is computer generated or completed by a staff member because I emailed and tried to call and nothing. I had shopped at Ashley's before, but after this experience, I went and shopped around. I bought several dinning room sets, beds/mattresses, and recliners at National Furniture Liquidators. I know some people may believe the quality may not be up to par, but just like Ashley's Furniture, it's made overseas. When I had issues at National Furniture, I spoke to Mark and it was corrected on the spot. Not everyone would agree, but my furniture shopping experience at Ashley's was far worse than the shopping at National Furniture and I didn't have to stress out.

Back in the beginning of September, my wife and I came in to look for a new mattress and ended up spending a fortune on a king size TempurPedic LuxeBreeze, Adustable smart base, and an expensive storage headboard and footboard. Almost a $10,000.00 purchase. We had a delivery date for 2 weeks from our order time and we didn't find out until the supposed day of delivery that the mattress wasn't even in the distribution center. Even more frustrating was the fact that we were the ones who had to get to the bottom of it ourselves. We called and spoke with the store and they were completely unhelpful. We were foolish enough to buy into the new promise date and waited again to find out again on the new supposed delivery date that it STILL wasn't going to be delivered for another 2 weeks. We decided that we were tired of the horrible communication and decided to go in to return it. When we spoke with a customer service representative, he made the excuse that it wasn't their fault and blamed the delivery company. We agreed to wait and about a week later we received a call to confirm our new delivery date. We felt confident that it was going to work out this time, since we received multiple phone calls, text messages, and emails all confirming the date. We took another day off of work and waited eagerly for the 7:15 AM delivery that we were promised and at 7:20 AM, yet again, we received another call to inform us that we would have to wait another 10 days. The sheer and utter lack of communication is abhorrent. The only reason that we ever found anything out, was because we had to jump through hoops to figure out what the heck was going on. I had to pester Crystal, who made the mistake of giving us her number and telling us to text if we needed anything. She rarely responded and when she did, it was days later after we became increasingly more frustrated at her lack of communication, despite her promises to keep us in the loop. We would have been more than happy to wait for our order if we had any idea of what was going on, but to find out THE DAY OF, EVERY. SINGLE. TIME, was absolutely unacceptable. Perhaps the WORST customer service that we've EVER received. We have since returned the entire order and will be taking our money elsewhere. Ashley will likely never have our business again. To reiterate. We weren't upset at the delay. We were disappointed in the horrible communication and bad customer service. Had we received updates PRIOR to taking time our of our busy schedules, we wouldn't have minded, but we lost valuable time and embarrassingly had to keep putting in time off requests for the SAME supposed delivery.

A 1 Star Rating is far too generous... After remodeling our home and discarding most of our furniture we were in need of replacements. This place is a joke and the constant delays will make your head spin. Being lawyers my wife and I are exploring options for breach of contract. Be warned. If you order from this place do not expect ANY of your furniture, except maybe a mattress with no bedframe...

I almost never write reviews, and poor ones at that, but I'm getting nowhere on the phone, so writing this as a last-ditch effort to reach someone useful in Customer Service. Ordered online during Memorial Day sale, knowing that it would be at least 6-10 weeks for delivery, and well-aware of Covid supply-chain issues. I was pleasantly surprised when I was able to select July 15th as a delivery date, and I received an email confirmation for this date. However, I never got a call to set the timeframe for the delivery, and since I wouldn't be available in the afternoon 7/15, I called Customer Service ahead of time and they said they switched the Delivery to 7/16. That date came & went with no delivery. I called, and they perplexed I'd even been offered a 7/16 delivery, as the sofa wasn't even in the warehouse yet (!?) However, they said it would be arriving, and rescheduled delivery to the following week 7/23. On 7/22, I hadn't gotten a delivery timeframe yet, so I called the main Customer Service line. They claimed I wasn't scheduled for delivery at all, but that the sofa was in the Albuquerque warehouse and suggested I call the local store. I did, and after several lengthy holds, was told delivery could be scheduled for the 26th, 28th, or 31st. I worked the 26th & 28th, so chose the 31st, and was promised THIS time, I would definitely be scheduled. I felt optimistic, because I soon received an automated text saying "Your home furnishings are ready for scheduling!" and to pick one of three dates (7/31, 8/3, or 8/4); I selected 7/31 as we'd discussed. I then received another "Scheduled Delivery Confirmation" email for the 31st. But today is the afternoon of 7/30, and I still hadn't gotten the call/text I was promised for the delivery window, so I called the store to inquire. They told me Not only am I not on the schedule for tomorrow, but that my sofa is NOT in the warehouse (as I'd been told last week by 2 separate representatives, and as implied by the text that it was available for scheduling), and that it was estimated to be in the warehouse with earliest delivery on August 6th. So this will be my third consecutive week that my delivery has been "scheduled," only for them to claim it cannot be scheduled until the following week. Not ONCE has anyone reached out to me to notify me of the delays or explain them; I have only discovered each delay by calling on my own. I would not be upset if the delivery took 8 to 12+ weeks *if* I'd been told that up front; however, I am upset because I am told every single week that it will be delivered Next Week, and it never is! The representative today told me that all of my previous dates were "estimated" delivery dates, but delivery is never *actually* scheduled until 24-48 hours prior. If that is the case, it is dishonest for the company to send correspondence titled "Scheduled Delivery Confirmation." Their emails also say, "If there are any changes, we'll contact you"-- This has also proven false. In sum, while I accept there can be valid reasons for delays in delivery, there is absolutely no excuse for the misleading communication I've experienced. Each time I have been "scheduled," I've blocked off the entire day to be home, only to be disappointed again. I am shocked how little the company has offered in the way of an explanation for the contradictory and disingenuous messages I've received; how little respect they've shown for all the time I (and apparently many other customers) have set aside waiting for them; and that they haven't offered any form of service recovery, such as waiving the [not insignificant] delivery fee. Their lack of concern or sympathy for my customer experience has been remarkable. Yes, I want my sofa, but really I just want someone to value my time by honestly telling me when it will ACTUALLY arrive, and following through with it.

TL;DR: Would have been a 2 star review and a cancelled order if it were not for Erica, who single handedly turned it all around! Heres the full review: I wish I could break out my rating by department, but since I cant, I gave a 5 star review (but thats primarily due to Erica - full story below). Here is my breakdown of the star ratings I would give if I could rate different aspects of my experience with Ashley Furniture: Sales: 5 stars Call center support: 2 stars (people were mostly nice, but overall zero help) Erica with In-store customer service: 5+++ stars Our initial sales experience back in December was great. Helpful associates, quick, friendly and personable service. Our sales guy helped find solutions for our bedroom and called in other team members for additional support for questions we had. He was very accommodating! After that, things took a turn; Every call to find out the status over 3+ months was hit or miss. Most call center reps were helpful enough, but were providing disappointing news that our order was pushed out further and further. One call center rep was downright rude, but thats neither here nor there. Hopefully that person was just having a bad day and doesnt talk to everyone like that... After over 3 months of continuing disappointment, a final call to the call center and the news that my order was pushed out another 2 months, we hit the breaking point. My husband and I decided to drive to the store and cancel our order of a full bedroom set, a few additional pieces for our room, and a full leather sectional. We walked up to the customer service area at the back of the store, told Erica that we would like to cancel completely, and she said OK. Half expecting to have to defend my decision and express my disappointment, I was surprised at her willingness to accommodate. She looked up our order, saw it was waiting on 3 missing pieces and that it was placed awhile ago and simply asked if I can find the pieces in our inventory, would you want to keep it? We said sure! She took a good bit of time identifying each piece in their inventory and solidified a delivery date of less than a week away! Simply amazing! Erica saved the entire sale by simply looking at our order, identifying the issue and rectifying the situation. I truly anticipated push back on the cancellation and/or an attempt at placating us with a discount or credit toward another purchase. There was none of that silliness, just solutions, and I am very happy for that! She was delightful to talk to and personally, I think she should get a bonus for saving the sale! :) Not sure it really works that way, but maybe her boss will read this and treat her to lunch or a coffee or something!

I ordered 2 items online (table and couch), during Black Friday sales of last year (end of November 2020), because they were good looking products for surprisingly very little money. I was told up front that the kitchen table I ordered would be multiple months out, which I was fine with because I had a table that would last until it arrived. And sure enough, 3 months later, I got a notification the table would be delivered, and then it arrived. I'm giving this a 2-star and not a 1-star because of the table, which I had no issues with, The issue I had was with my couch order... I had a 4-piece sectional couch that did not fit in my new living room, so I was downsizing. I ordered this smaller couch from Ashley on 11/28/2020, and had an email notification soon thereafter that the couch was scheduled to be delivered on 12/5/2020. So I listed my couch for sale, and managed to sell it the day before the couch was set to arrive. The 5th came and went, with no call or couch. I then get another notification about a delivery date of 12/15/2020. Before that date comes, I get a notification of a 12/18/2020 arrival, and then again a 12/28/2020 arrival, followed by 1/2/2021 and 1/13/2021. I had called into the support line for Ashley throughout these notifications, and they told me there was a bug in the system, and that the only "real" notification is if I get a phone call. Sure enough, I received 2 phone calls from Ashley representatives asking to schedule a delivery date. Both times, they gave me their available delivery dates/times, and I confirmed a date/time. Those days came and passed. The most frustrating part of this whole process was the customer service...I probably talked to 40-50 Ashley reps over the course of this process, and first off, they had no record of the calls I received to schedule the couch delivery, the tickets that I had created, any of the reps I had talked to previously, and basically no sort of accounting software keeping track of anything. Secondly, each person seemed to be pulling a number out of their @$$ about when my couch was scheduled to be delivered. I would talk to 2 or 3 people the same day and they would all give me different arrival days in the next 2 weeks. Eventually, around February, the scheduled delivery date was set to April 20th, and Ashley reps/managers were saying it was not yet a created product or available in any of their warehouses, but that it would be in April. So, because it was such a cheap couch, and my fiancee and I were now used to sitting on lawn chairs in our empty living room, I decided to just wait it out. The week prior to April 20th, I called into their automated system to make sure it hadn't changed, which it hadn't. But that day came and went without a phone call. I talked again with Ashley managers who said the updated delivery date was now June, and that they could offer me a $30 IN-STORE CREDIT (that expired in 3 months) for the inconvenience. Needless to say I canceled the order and spent a little more money to walk into Mor Furniture for Less and walk out with a couch that same day *thank you, Mor, you gave me a place to rest my weary head*. Long story short, Ashley Furniture Online (I can't speak for in-store, because the reps I spoke to made it very apparent they are basically 2 completely different companies with no communication between them) creates a product that apparently doesn't exist until after you order it, and then they scramble to design, build, and ship it, which takes at least 6 months to do. If you read this, Ashley, fix the bug in your system sending bogus email notifications ASAP, and figure out some way to actually deliver the products you are selling. And if this is related to the single product I happened to order (Darcy Sofa), then remove that product from your inventory. It obviously doesn't exist.
